Program: The Why Factor
Title: Pleasure: Why We Like the Things We Like
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03hlfl2
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 15 Feb 2016
Why do we like the things that we like? At the root of it is 3, 4 -Dihydroxyphenethylamine - or Dopamine - a chemical produced by the nerve cells in the brain to signal to others. But as Mike Williams finds out our pleasure circuit can be triggered by some obvious and not so obvious things. (Photo: a young woman listens to music on headphones. Credit to Shutterstock) Show less